An overview of the development of the genre and style of installation art. Tradition and innovation in installation. Sculptural and conceptual solutions. Practical work. The use of ready-made and found materials, assemblage.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Course is directed to the students in magister level for giving introduction to the installation as one of possibilities for conceptual artistic expression. For the end of the course every student creates own work in the level for exhibition.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course student:
-has an ability to create artwork of the installation using ready-made materials and objects;
-has understanding and know-how of conceptual artwork, for analysing and recreating objects in different environment;
-knows how to use text, sounds, and other space related aspects;
-has an ability to create own artwork ready for exhibiting.
